  "claim_short": "2508.14603 Similarities of subspace lattices in Banach spaces isometric complement counterexample likely valid. Source Section 3.3 asks whether a complement of Grp(Alg(L)) in Col(L) can consist of isometric operators. Counterexample: X=C^2 with norm ||(z,w)||=max(|z|,|w|,|z+w/2|), M=Ce1, N=Ce2, L={0,M,N,X}. Then Col(L) is the monomial group and Grp(Alg(L)) is the diagonal subgroup, so it has an algebraic S2...",
